Implemented the source change in:

- `logstash-core/src/main/java/org/logstash/common/BufferedTokenizerExt.java`

What changed:
- Centralized buffered RubyString insertion through `appendToInput(...)`.
- The helper explicitly uses `RubyArray.append(IRubyObject)` and documents why Java collection methods such as `add`/`addAll` must not be used: they can route `RubyString` values through Java string conversion and alter byte encoding.

